  <title>Anglerfish main page</title>
  <link rel="import" href="/header.html">
 <body>  
  <p>Anglerfish is a method of determining the orientation of an &alpha;-helix relative to a defined axis in a rotationally symmetric protein structure such as a membrane protein channel. This axis (Axis in the figure) is the axis of rotational symmetry within the structure, which is defined as the normal to a plane containing the C atoms of a given residue from each monomer (A). For example, given a channel this will be the pore axis. The helix is defined between a start residue (N) and end residue (C).Â The orientation is split into 2 components:<br>The tilt (&theta;t): the angle between the helix and a parallel to the axis at N.<br>The swing (&theta;s): the angle between the axis and C at N in the plane perpendicular to the axis.</p>
<p>For more information on running anglerfish see the<a href="help.html"> help</a> page or the <a href="https://www.google.co.uk/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=2&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwjRrJCRqIPUAhWhC8AKHRX5DQUQFggsMAE&url=https%3A%2F%2Fbioinformatics.oxfordjournals.org%2Fcontent%2Fearly%2F2016%2F12%2F29%2Fbioinformatics.btw781.full.pdf%2Bhtml&usg=AFQjCNGcXv-mpSklYnE0vZuLHPB9UAg7YA&sig2=2chrNPTqBJ4dI_pm23TMQw"> paper: </a> Colledge and Wallace (2016) Bioinformatics 33(8), 1233-1234 </p>
  <img src="axisdefinition.png" alt="axis_definition" style="width:191px;height:284px;padding:20px;align:center;">
  <img src="angledefinition.png" alt="angle_definition" style="width:186px;height:274px;padding:20px;align:center;">
  <p>To run Anglerfish you will need:
  <ul>
   <li>A PDB file containing a symmetric homomer with at least 3 chains</li>
   <li>The number of start and end residues of the helix in question in the PDB file</li>
   <li>The number of any residue that is symmetric in all chains to define the axis</li>
  </ul>
  </p>
  <form action="../cgi-bin/anglerfish.pl" name="input" method="post" ENCTYPE = "multipart/form-data">
